cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Assevra or report a score measured with it, please cite this project."
title: "Assevra: A Reliability Scorecard for LLM Agents"
abstract: >-
  Assevra is an open reference implementation and a named methodology (the
  Assevra Reliability Scorecard) for measuring the reliability of LLM agents
  across four dimensions: grounding/faithfulness, safety/refusal, PII-leak, and
  task-completion. Each dimension is scored with an explicit method (LLM-as-judge
  or deterministic), a stated pass threshold, and a reported confidence interval.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Divi
    given-names: Veera Ravindra
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-07-04"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/assevra/assevra"
keywords:
  - LLM
  - AI agents
  - reliability
  - evaluation
  - LLM-as-judge
  - grounding
  - PII
  - safety
